FBIS4-24246 "drafr124_e_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria National Constitutional Conference Begins in Abuja National Constitutional Conference Begins in Abuja Taraba Delegate Replaced AB2706131094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1200 GMT 27 Jun 94 AB2706131094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network English BFN [Text] The head of state, General Sani Abacha, has appointed Mr. (Saleh Abubakar) to replace Alhaji Abubakar Barde from Taraba State as the government's nominated delegate to the Constitutional Conference, which has begun today. The replacement of Alhaji Abubakar Barde followed information that he was one of those already elected to the conference. A statement by the secretary to the Government of the Federation, Alhaji Aminu Saleh, advised the new nominee to proceed to Abuja immediately for the conference as one of the three nominees from Taraba State.
